</li><li> There's also the <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/UsefulNotes/GameGear" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/UsefulNotes/GameGear">Game Gear</a> game <em><a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VideoGame/SonicLabyrinth" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VideoGame/SonicLabyrinth">Sonic Labyrinth</a></em> and the <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/UsefulNotes/ArcadeGame" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/UsefulNotes/ArcadeGame">Arcade Game</a> <em><a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VideoGame/SegaSonicTheHedgehog" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VideoGame/SegaSonicTheHedgehog">SegaSonic the Hedgehog</a></em>.
</li></ul></li><li> <em><a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VideoGame/CoolSpot" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VideoGame/CoolSpot">Spot Goes To Hollywood</a></em>
</li><li> <em><a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VideoGame/SuperMario3DLand" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VideoGame/SuperMario3DLand">Super Mario 3D Land</a></em> uses this in certain areas, most likely as an <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/Homage" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/Homage">homage</a> to <em>Super Mario RPG</em>. These tend to use <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ForcedPerspective" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ForcedPerspective">Forced Perspective</a> when it comes to jumping on platforms and footholds.
</li></ul></div>
